formatted_address: 503 W Coast Dr, #01-73 Ayer Rajah Food Centre, Singapore 120503
name: Abdhus Salam Rojak

reviews.text:
The spiced peanut sauce, although having a very nice mouthfeel and texture, is a bit too sweet to my liking. The content variety and quality are just okay but during my visit the tempeh seemed to be not in the best condition (though still perfectly edible). Perhaps I came at the wrong timing.

Chiming from other prior comments, I wish the pricing could've been more honest. Bought 5 pieces (like medu vada, fish cake, egg vada kind of stuffs, no 'fancy' items like beef lung) and charged $7 even though the seller initially said it was $5.
I like the taste of gravy not too light or thick and items rojak oil fried when ordered. Food wise no complaints. Grumpy Guy behind counter doesn't smile so don't get offended.
Tried the Indian rojak and really enjoyed itâ€”especially the sauce, which was rich and flavorful. The price is reasonable, and Iâ€™ll definitely come back again!

This will be my last time patronising this stall due to their exorbitant prices and dishonesty. I got a plate of Indian rojak with 3 items (potato, fishcake & tau hu) and was asked to pay $8! Thinking that probably due to inflation, I continued with my order. To my surprise, when I received my dish, I found my potato had shrinked by half the size. I questioned them to check if they left it out by mistake, and they can tell me that the potato is small sized. Knowing that it is fruitless arguing, I walked away.

The famous origin of Salam Rojak. Situated within West Coast area, stall 01-73 will be brightly & easily to find. Eating rojak here with their hot fried, this the best moment to consume it there. The sweet flavour gravy will much make you unstoppable eating their rojak. Their collective food item will be stack nicely, you just need to choose one by one.
